benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Retrieve invoice item tags

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01, @TC05, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC10, @TC11, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC16, @TC17, @TC19, @TC23, @TC24, @TC26, @TC27 cover successful retrieval, invalid IDs, missing parameters, and state variations.
Empty Response: @TC05 covers case when no tags exist for an invoice item.

Query Parameters: Multiple scenarios (@TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC06, @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC16, @TC17, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25) test various combinations of optional parameters, including includedDeleted, audit levels, extra parameters, and maximum/minimum UUID lengths.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized access or invalid tokens beyond @TC12.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate high request volume or rate limiting behavior.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
System Error Handling: Limited coverage of backend failures (@TC18, @TC25) only in specific contexts; broader error scenarios missing.
Security: While some security tests (@TC19, @TC20) are included, more comprehensive injection or XSS tests could be added.
Performance: Basic load tests (@TC21, @TC22) are mentioned but not detailed in scenarios.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large datasets.
Include explicit authorization tests to ensure proper 401/403 responses for invalid or missing tokens.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system stability under high load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Expand security testing with more injection, XSS, and other vulnerability scenarios.
Develop detailed performance testing scenarios under various load conditions.
Include tests for backend service unavailability and recovery to improve robustness.
